arch:property.oc:show_val: Locus 1 is a layer of wash and overburden covering the West Precinct Wall. It is a loose reddish brown silt and sand (Munsell 5 YR 5/4). It has a medium amount of bones, plaster, sand, and shells, and a large amount of pottery and stones.
Wash and debris covering the West Precinct Wall.
61.8 m north south-by- unknown east west.
Phase XIII: Major collapses continue into the Islamic period.
